The	overall	workflow	involves	the	following	steps:			1)	input	gene	expression/metabolomics	data	files,		2)	filter	data	sets	by	gene	and	metabolite	abundances	and	imputed	values,		3)	 run	 linear	 models	 on	 all	 possible	 gene-metabolites	 pairs	 and	 extract	 FDR-adjusted	interaction	p-values,		4)	filter	results	by	FDR-adjusted	p-values	and	Spearman	correlation	differences,		5)	plot/visualize	user-defined	gene-metabolite	associations			The	package,	source	code,	vignettes,	and	formatted	datasets	used	in	to	produce	results	in	this	manuscript	are	available	for	download	on	GitHub	(https://github.com/mathelab/IntLIM).
